COSMOSformat

Class COSMOScontentFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • COSMOSformat.COSMOScontentFormat
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    V0Component, V1Component, V2Component, V3Component

    public class COSMOScontentFormat
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the base class for the COSMOS Strong Motion Data Format. It extracts a channel record from the input file and parses it into its various pieces. Each COSMOS file type (V0-3) differs only in the format of its data section. This base class defines the fields and methods common to all COSMOS files and lets the extending classes define their data sections.

      • loadComponent

        public int loadComponent(int start,
                         java.lang.String[] infile)
                  throws FormatException,
                         SmException
        This method extracts the current component/channel from the input file. It is set up to handle multiple components in the same file by starting at the given line number in the file and returning the line number at the end of the current component.
        Parameters:
        start - starting line in the file contents to parse the channel
        infile - array holding all the lines from the input file
        Returns:
        the line number after the end of the current component
        Throws:
        FormatException - if unable to extract expected values from text
        SmException - if unable to convert text to numeric

      • parseDataSection

        public int parseDataSection(int startLine,
                            java.lang.String[] infile)
                     throws FormatException
        This method must be overridden by each extended class. Since each COSMOS file differs only in the format of the data sections, each class extending this for a specific V type must define the process for extracting the data from the data arrays.
        Parameters:
        startLine - line number where data section starts
        infile - array containing each line of the input file
        Returns:
        the updated line number, after the data section
        Throws:
        FormatException - if unable to extract parameters from format line

      • VrecToText

        public java.lang.String[] VrecToText()
        This method must be overridden by each extending class. It is called to format the V component into its text file format for writing out to file.
        Returns:
        the contents of the V record in COSMOS format

      • checkForRcrdIdAndAuth

        public void checkForRcrdIdAndAuth()
        This method checks line 7 of the text header to see if it contains the record id, and checks the comments for the Authorization tag. If either of these are found they are saved for use in processing. If the SCNL tag is found and there is no defined channel number, the channel code from the SCNL tag is saved for the channel identifier.

      • updateEndOfDataLine

        public void updateEndOfDataLine(java.lang.String dtype,
                                java.lang.String channel)
        This method updates the End-of-data line to match the current processing type.
        Parameters:
        dtype - the data type to update the End-of-data line with, such as UNCORACC, CORACC, VELOCITY, or DISPLACE. If no match, then "response spectra" is used.
        channel - the channel identifier
